documentation.text: @dev List of allowed referral partners addresses
@notice Adds address to list of allowed referral partners
@notice Returns if passed address are listed as referral partner in the registry
@notice Returns current list of referral partners

natspec.author: psirex, dzhon

addReferralPartner(address,string).notice: Adds address to list of allowed referral partners

params._addReferralPartnerRoleHolders: List of addresses which will be     granted with role ADD_REFERRAL_PARTNER_ROLE
params._admin: Address which will be granted with role DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE
params._removeReferralPartnerRoleHolders: List of addresses which will     be granted with role REMOVE_REFERRAL_PARTNER_ROLE

getReferralPartners().notice: Returns current list of referral partners

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

isReferralPartner(address).notice: Returns if passed address are listed as referral partner in the registry

removeReferralPartner(address).details: To delete a referral partner from the referralPartners array in O(1), we swap the element to delete with the last one in the array, and then remove the last element (sometimes called as 'swap and pop').
removeReferralPartner(address).notice: Removes address from list of allowed referral partners

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

natspec.notice: Stores list of addresses with referral partners
